{
  "message": "fix(tests): use get_exit_code() for proper test exit status\n\nReplace `exit $?` with `exit \"$(get_exit_code)\"` in 18 test files.\n\nPreviously, tests exited with the return value of `print_results`,\nwhich could be 0 even when tests failed. Now tests properly return\nexit code 1 when any tests or assertions fail, and 0 only when all\npass.\n\nThis ensures CI pipelines correctly detect test failures.\n\n\ud83e\udd16 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
